<p>I'm trying to create an element to config parameter by touching it, on angular and it most work on mobil devices. To do that i need to detect de touch position relative to the element. But i'm having a lot of troubles with it. First of all, android and ios browser don't have a common way of doing it. Also only i was able to do it, it's manual, and not understandable. Also wasn't able to make it work on crosswalk.</p>  <p>Here is my element</p>  <pre><code>angular.module('angularTouchWidgets.directives.timerEditor', [])      .directive('timerEditor', function () {         return {             restrict: "E",             scope: { time: '=' },             template:'&lt;div style="margin: auto; height: 250px; width: 350px;" on-drag-start="onDrag($event)" on-touch="onTouch($event)" on-drag-end="onRelease()" on-drag="drag($event)"&gt;\                     &lt;svg id="clock-editor" height="250" width="350"&gt;\                         &lt;defs&gt;\                             &lt;filter id="shadow-{{$id}}" x="-200%" y="-200%" width="450%" height="450%"&gt;\                                 &lt;feOffset result="offOut" in="SourceGraphic" dx="0" dy="2"&gt;&lt;/feOffset&gt;\                                 &lt;feColorMatrix result="matrixOut" in="offOut" type="matrix" values="0.4 0 0 0 0 0 0.4 0 0 0 0 0 0.4 0 0 0 0 0 1 0"&gt;&lt;/feColorMatrix&gt;\                                 &lt;feGaussianBlur result="blurOut" in="matrixOut" stdDeviation="2"&gt;&lt;/feGaussianBlur&gt;\                                 &lt;feBlend in="SourceGraphic" in2="blurOut" mode="normal"&gt;&lt;/feBlend&gt;\                             &lt;/filter&gt;\                         &lt;/defs&gt;\                         &lt;g&gt;\                             &lt;circle cx="175" cy="125" r="100" fill="white"&gt;&lt;/circle&gt;\                             &lt;path fill="#eee" d="M 175 25 A 100 100 0 0 1 225 38L 175 125"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;\                             &lt;path fill="#eee" d="M 261 75 A 100 10